<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="571" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1596,1802]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">
Seven species are now known in this genus, all from southeast Asia. These range from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,326,1634,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Asprothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seminigricornis">
<emphasis box="[151,326,1634,1657]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">seminigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a white species with black antennal apices, to species with the body bicoloured or dark and the wings variously coloured. Two of the species have become widespread, presumably through the trade in horticultural produce. One of these, 
<taxonomicName box="[554,691,1705,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Asprothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculatus">
<emphasis box="[554,691,1705,1730]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">bimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[930,1054,1705,1730]" name="Martinique" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">Martinique</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Michel" box="[1068,1382,1705,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" refString="Michel, B. &amp; Ryckewaert, P. (2014) Asprothrips bimaculatus sp. n. (Thripidae, Dendrothripinae) from Martinique. Zootaxa, 3793, 496 - 498. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.4.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Michel &amp; Ryckewaert 
<number box="[1324,1382,1706,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and subsequently recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[481,548,1741,1766]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[610,713,1741,1766]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tong" box="[730,931,1741,1766]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" refString="Tong, X. L., Wang, Z. H. &amp; Mirab-Balou, M. (2016) Two new species and one new record of the genus Asprothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) from China. Zootaxa, 4061 (2), 181 - 188." type="journal article" year="2016">
Tong 
<emphasis box="[800,853,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[870,931,1741,1766]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" value="2016.0">2016</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The other, 
<taxonomicName box="[1081,1257,1742,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Asprothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seminigricornis">
<emphasis box="[1081,1257,1742,1765]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">seminigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[212,315,1777,1802]" name="Australia" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">Australia</collectingCountry>
but has been found widely around the world (Mound 
<emphasis box="[920,969,1777,1802]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[983,1044,1777,1802]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" value="2016.0">2016</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
